      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Like the chances of SOUTHAMPTON FLARE (1) who is a seven-start maiden having his first run for the new yard. Well-travelled starting career in Victoria then in NSW and Qld but finds himself in a new yard fitter for two runs from a spell and close to a win. Looks the one to beat on best figures. GOD'S EYE (2) has had three runs for the Cole yard since coming from Victoria and is yet to race in maiden grade. Drops back to the right class now and gets a chance to find his best. Same goes for SASSY ABBEY (5) who raced in the same race as GOD'S EYE last time which was a Class 2 and finished midfield. Back to maiden grade and will go close. LADY FIREBALL (4) drew off the track on debut and was safely held but can improve sharply. AQUA BLUE (3) has been well beaten all three runs and others look better.",
